20	Calculus with Vectors	\N	["Jay S. Treiman"]	Springer	2014-10-30	3319094386	9783319094380	en	406	["Mathematics"]	Calculus with Vectors grew out of a strong need for a beginning calculus textbook for undergraduates who intend to pursue careers in STEM fields. The approach introduces vector-valued functions from the start, emphasizing the connections between one-variable and multi-variable calculus. The text includes early vectors and early transcendentals and includes a rigorous but informal approach to vectors. Examples and focused applications are well presented along with an abundance of motivating exercises. The approaches taken to topics such as the derivation of the derivatives of sine and cosine, the approach to limits and the use of "tables" of integration have been modified from the standards seen in other textbooks in order to maximize the ease with which students may comprehend the material. Additionally, the material presented is intentionally non-specific to any software or hardware platform in order to accommodate the wide variety and rapid evolution of tools used. Technology is referenced in the text and is required for a good number of problems.	https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9783319094380-M.jpg?default=false	https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=br0hBQAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api	textbook	google_books	br0hBQAAQBAJ	{"average_rating":5,"ratings_count":1,"info_link":"https:\\/\\/play.google.com\\/store\\/books\\/details?id=br0hBQAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api","canonical_volume_link":"https:\\/\\/play.google.com\\/store\\/books\\/details?id=br0hBQAAQBAJ","reader_link":"https:\\/\\/play.google.com\\/books\\/reader?id=br0hBQAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api","embeddable":true,"viewability":"PARTIAL","text_to_speech_permission":"ALLOWED","public_domain":false,"pdf_available":true,"pdf_download_link":null,"epub_available":true,"epub_download_link":null}	1	2026-05-16 09:34:48	2026-05-16 09:34:48	approved	\N	\N
