179	Deep Reinforcement Learning: Emerging Trends in Macroeconomics and Future Prospects	\N	["Tohid Atashbar","Rui Aruhan Shi"]	International Monetary Fund	2022-12-16	\N	9798400224713	en	32	["Business & Economics"]	The application of Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) in economics has been an area of active research in recent years. A number of recent works have shown how deep reinforcement learning can be used to study a variety of economic problems, including optimal policy-making, game theory, and bounded rationality. In this paper, after a theoretical introduction to deep reinforcement learning and various DRL algorithms, we provide an overview of the literature on deep reinforcement learning in economics, with a focus on the main applications of deep reinforcement learning in macromodeling. Then, we analyze the potentials and limitations of deep reinforcement learning in macroeconomics and identify a number of issues that need to be addressed in order for deep reinforcement learning to be more widely used in macro modeling.	https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9798400224713-M.jpg?default=false	https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=BISkEAAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api	textbook	google_books	BISkEAAAQBAJ	{"average_rating":null,"ratings_count":null,"info_link":"https:\\/\\/books.google.co.in\\/books?id=BISkEAAAQBAJ&dq=machine+learning&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api","canonical_volume_link":"https:\\/\\/books.google.com\\/books\\/about\\/Deep_Reinforcement_Learning_Emerging_Tre.html?hl=&id=BISkEAAAQBAJ","reader_link":"https:\\/\\/play.google.com\\/books\\/reader?id=BISkEAAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api","embeddable":true,"viewability":"PARTIAL","text_to_speech_permission":"ALLOWED","public_domain":false,"pdf_available":true,"pdf_download_link":null,"epub_available":false,"epub_download_link":null}	1	2026-05-16 10:09:03	2026-05-16 10:09:03	approved	\N	\N
