ral_Calculus.html?hl=&id=dh4Y7YgeoeAC";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=dh4Y7YgeoeAC&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:4;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"dl1jDwAAQBAJ";s:5:"title";s:110:"A Textbook of B.Sc. Mathematics (Differential Calculus) (For 1st Year, 1st Semester of Telangana Universities)";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:1:{i:0;s:93:"Rao, Venkateswara V., Murthy, Krishna N., Sarma B.V.S.S., Sastry Anjaneya S. & Ranganatham S.";}s:9:"publisher";s:19:"S. Chand Publishing";s:14:"published_date";N;s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"9352830385";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9789352830381";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:362;s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:11:"Mathematics";}s:11:"description";s:31:"A Textbook of B.Sc. Mathematics";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9789352830381-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=dl1jDwAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=dl1jDwAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";i:5;s:13:"ratings_count";i:1;s:9:"info_link";s:74:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dl1jDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:59:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dl1jDwAAQBAJ";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=dl1jDwAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:5;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"dKnmDwAAQBAJ";s:5:"title";s:64:"A Textbook of B.Sc. Mathematics Differential & Integral Calculus";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:1:{i:0;s:108:"V Venkateswara Rao, N Krishnamurthy, B V S S Sarma, S Anjaneya Sastry  \nS Ranganatham & Dr. R Bharavi Sharma";}s:9:"publisher";s:19:"S. Chand Publishing";s:14:"published_date";N;s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"9352837835";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9789352837830";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:248;s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:7:"Science";}s:11:"description";s:64:"A Textbook of B.Sc. Mathematics Differential & Integral Calculus";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9789352837830-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=dKnmDwAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=dKnmDwAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";N;s:13:"ratings_count";N;s:9:"info_link";s:74:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dKnmDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:59:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=dKnmDwAAQBAJ";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=dKnmDwAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:6;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"v87WDQAAQBAJ";s:5:"title";s:46:"AP® Calculus AB & BC All Access Book + Online";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:1:{i:0;s:12:"Stu Schwartz";}s:9:"publisher";s:27:"Research & Education Assoc.";s:14:"published_date";s:10:"2017-01-04";s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"0738687944";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9780738687940";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:435;s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:10:"Study Aids";}s:11:"description";s:3446:"All Access for the AP® Calculus AB & BC Exams Book + Web + Mobile Updated for the new 2017 Exams Everything you need to prepare for the Advanced Placement® Calculus exams, in a study system built around you! There are many different ways to prepare for an Advanced Placement® exam. What's best for you depends on how much time you have to study and how comfortable you are with the subject matter. To score your highest, you need a system that can be customized to fit you: your schedule, your learning style, and your current level of knowledge. This book, and the online tools that come with it, will help you personalize your AP® Calculus prep by testing your understanding, pinpointing your weaknesses, and delivering flashcard study materials unique to you. REA's All Access system allows you to create a personalized study plan through three simple steps: targeted review of exam content, assessment of your knowledge, and focused study in the topics where you need the most help. Here's how it works: Review the Book: Study the topics tested on the AP® Calculus AB & BC exams and learn proven strategies that will help you tackle any question you may see on test day. Test Yourself and Get Feedback: As you review the book, test yourself with 9 end-of-chapter quizzes and 3 mini-tests. Score reports from your free online tests and quizzes give you a fast way to pinpoint what you really know and what you should spend more time studying. Improve Your Score: Armed with your score reports, you can personalize your study plan. Review the parts of the book where you are weakest, and use the REA Study Center to create your own unique e-flashcards, adding to the 100 free cards included with this book. Visit The REA Study Center for a suite of online tools: The best way to personalize your study plan is to get frequent feedback on what you know and what you don't know. At the online REA Study Center, you can access three types of assessment: topic-level quizzes, mini-tests, and a full-length practice test. Each of these tools provides true-to-format questions and delivers a detailed score report that follows the topics set by the College Board®. Topic Level Quizzes: Short, 15-minute quizzes are available throughout the review and test your immediate understanding of the topics just covered. Mini-Tests: Three online mini-tests cover what you've studied. These tests are like the actual AP® exam, only shorter, and will help you evaluate your overall understanding of the subject. 2 Full-Length Practice Tests - (1 for Calculus AB and 1 for Calculus BC): After you've finished reviewing the book, take our full-length practice exams to practice under test-day conditions. Available both in the book and online, these tests give you the most complete picture of your strengths and weaknesses. We strongly recommend you take the online versions of the exams for the added benefits of timed testing, automatic scoring, and a detailed score report. Improving Your Score with e-Flashcards: With your score reports from the quizzes and tests, you'll be able to see exactly which AP® Calculus topics you need to review. Use this information to create your own flashcards for the areas where you are weak. And, because you will create these flashcards through the REA Study Center, you can access them from any computer or smartphone. REA's All Access test prep is a must-have for students taking the AP® Calculus AB & BC exams!";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9780738687940-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=v87WDQAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=v87WDQAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:14:"epub_available";b:1;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";N;s:13:"ratings_count";N;s:9:"info_link";s:74:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=v87WDQAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:59:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=v87WDQAAQBAJ";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=v87WDQAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:1;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:7;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"MBd5BiG1R8wC";s:5:"title";s:21:"Differential Calculus";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:1:{i:0;s:17:"S Balachandra Rao";}s:9:"publisher";s:21:"New Age International";s:14:"published_date";s:4:"1992";s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"8122403085";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9788122403084";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:540;s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:8:"Calculus";}s:11:"description";s:1892:"This Book Is Designed To Be Used For Class-Room Teaching For A Course In Differential Calculus At The Undergraduate Level And Also As A Reference Book For Others Who Need The Use Of Differential Calculus. The Book Is Designed In Accordance With The Syllabus In Differential Calculus Prescribed In Most Of The Indian Universities.The Following Are Some Of The Special Features Of This Textbook: * In Addition To The Theoretical Treatment Of The Topics In Differential Calculus, Due Respect Is Given To Application-Oriented Approach Through Various Illustrations And Exercises Drawn From Practical Sciences. * The Graphical And Numerical Approach Provided In The Text Enhances The Appreciation And Understanding Of The Concepts Involved. * A Large Number Of Worked Examples And Exercises, With Answers, Drawn From Various Examination Papers Of Indian And Foreign Universities Are Included. * Biographical Notes And Historical Snippets Have Been Added With A View To Motivating And Inspiring The Students. Brief Life-Sketches And Contributions Of Great Mathematicians Like Sir Isaac Newton And Leibniz Form Part Of The Book. * The Unique And Pioneering Aspect Of The Present Book Is That A Large Number Of Computer Programs And Graphic Printouts For Various Topics Indifferential Calculus Are Included. The Fascinating Potential Of Graphics, For The Understanding Of Calculus, On A Computer Is Well Brought Out Through Computer Programs Which Can Be Readily Worked On An Ibm-Compatible Pc. Further, In Order To Make The Programs Useful To Students And Amateurs Who Have Access Only To The Popular Home-Computers Interesting Programs Which Can Be, Run On The Very Popular Bbc Microcomputer And Sinclair Spectrum Have Also Been Provided.Very Interesting Graphics Of Evolutes Of Famous Curves And Envelopes Of Families Of Curves Along With Their Ready-To-Work Programs Add To The Value Of The Book.";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9788122403084-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=MBd5BiG1R8wC&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=MBd5BiG1R8wC&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";N;s:13:"ratings_count";N;s:9:"info_link";s:100:"https://books.google.co.in/books?id=MBd5BiG1R8wC&dq=calculus+textbook&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:83:"https://books.google.com/books/about/Differential_Calculus.html?hl=&id=MBd5BiG1R8wC";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=MBd5BiG1R8wC&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:8;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"sdqLuwEACAAJ";s:5:"title";s:45:"Complete Calculus for Physics and Engineering";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:1:{i:0;s:14:"Henry Phillips";}s:9:"publisher";s:43:"Createspace Independent Publishing Platform";s:14:"published_date";s:10:"2018-08-31";s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"1726424197";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9781726424196";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:528;s:10:"categories";a:0:{}s:11:"description";s:2576:"This is a fairly standard level calculus textbook aimed at a first-year students. It was written by a master teacher at Massachusetts Institute of Technology whose calculus course there became nationally famous as a model for such courses before World War II. While this text focuses on applications and requires no more background then high school algebra and geometry, it differs from most standard textbooks, even of its contemporaries, in 2 major ways. Firstly, it's clearly more comprehensive and sophisticated then most of those textbooks and covers a number of topics that are usually not present, such as basic vector algebra and geometry, conic sections, determinants, parametric equations, numerical integration and basic complex analysis of the plane. The 2 chapters on complex analysis in a basic calculus text are particularly noteworthy. The growing importance of complex variables in the physical sciences had become generally accepted during the early years of World War II due to its applications in hydrodynamics, engineering and electromagnetic theory. These additional topics are also indicative of the target audience, which were beginning mathematics and physical science majors at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology in the early 1940's. Because they were preparing for careers in the technical fields, these students needed stronger and more diverse mathematical training for their future studies. Secondly, while not a rigorous mathematics textbook in the sense of real analysis or abstract algebra, it is certainly more careful then most calculus textbooks-either modern or classical-with many example calculations. For example, many limits and bounds are carefully computed with inequalities in the examples. Also, when available, Phillips gives a number of geometric proofs that are quite careful, particularly those with applications to physics and engineering. For example, a very clear geometric proof is given of the Squeeze Theorem. Indeed, in many ways, the working mathematical premises of the text appear to be a) focus on all tools and applications are that critical to the future training of physics and engineering students and b) Only give careful proofs of results when elementary methods using high school mathematics are available. No deep properties of the real numbers or topological properties are used beyond superficial use of the absolute value function. This outstanding textbook will help serious students of minimal background master calculus and lay the foundations for an in-depth study of the mathematical sciences.";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9781726424196-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=sdqLuwEACAAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=sdqLuwEACAAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:0;s:11:"viewability";s:8:"NO_PAGES";s:13:"pdf_available";b:0;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";N;s:13:"ratings_count";N;s:9:"info_link";s:100:"https://books.google.co.in/books?id=sdqLuwEACAAJ&dq=calculus+textbook&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:102:"https://books.google.com/books/about/Complete_Calculus_for_Physics_and_Engine.html?hl=&id=sdqLuwEACAAJ";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=sdqLuwEACAAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:0;s:11:"viewability";s:8:"NO_PAGES";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:0;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:9;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"hRbzDwAAQBAJ";s:5:"title";s:23:"Multi-Variable Calculus";s:8:"subtitle";s:12:"A First Step";s:7:"authors";a:1:{i:0;s:10:"Yunzhi Zou";}s:9:"publisher";s:30:"Walter de Gruyter GmbH & Co KG";s:14:"published_date";s:10:"2020-03-09";s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"3110674378";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9783110674378";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:336;s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:11:"Mathematics";}s:11:"description";s:413:"This book is a concise yet complete calculus textbook covering all essential topics in multi-variable calculus, including geometry in three-dimensional space, partial derivatives, maximum/minimum, multiple integrals and vector calculus as well as a chapter for ODE. All the chapters are constructed in a logical way to outline the essence of each topic and to address potential difficulties arising from learning.";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9783110674378-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=hRbzDwAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=hRbzDwAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";N;s:13:"ratings_count";N;s:9:"info_link";s:74:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=hRbzDwAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:59:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=hRbzDwAAQBAJ";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=hRbzDwAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:10;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"x0zc1sBl_VUC";s:5:"title";s:21:"Differential Calculus";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:1:{i:0;s:11:"H. S. Dhami";}s:9:"publisher";s:21:"New Age International";s:14:"published_date";s:4:"2007";s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"8122411460";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9788122411461";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:422;s:10:"categories";a:0:{}s:11:"description";s:1043:"Differential Calculus, An Outgrowth Of The Problems Concerned With Slope Of Curved Lines And The Areas Enclosed By Them Has Developed So Much That Texts Are Required Which May Lead The Students Directly To The Heart Of The Subject And Prepare Them For Challenges Of The Field. The Present Book Is An Attempt In This Regard. An Excellent Book On Differential Calculus This Book Has Been Meticulously Planned And Numerous Solved Examples Have Been Selected To Make The Subject Interesting; Besides Problems Are Given At The End Of Each Main Theorem Which Supplement The Text And By Solving Them The Reader Can Judge His Level Of Understanding Of The Given Facts.Exercises Have Been Framed By Arranging Questions In Such A Manner That After Doing Illustrative Examples, One Should Not Feel Difficulty In Solving Any Problem. Considerable Material Has Been Included Here That Covers A Large Number Of Courses. This Has Been Done To Make The Book More Flexible, To Provide A Useful Book Of Reference And To Stimulate Further Interest In The Topics.";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9788122411461-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=x0zc1sBl_VUC&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=x0zc1sBl_VUC&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";N;s:13:"ratings_count";N;s:9:"info_link";s:100:"https://books.google.co.in/books?id=x0zc1sBl_VUC&dq=calculus+textbook&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:83:"https://books.google.com/books/about/Differential_Calculus.html?hl=&id=x0zc1sBl_VUC";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=x0zc1sBl_VUC&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:11;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"FM-lEAAAQBAJ";s:5:"title";s:42:"Analysing Historical Mathematics Textbooks";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:1:{i:0;s:14:"Gert Schubring";}s:9:"publisher";s:15:"Springer Nature";s:14:"published_date";s:10:"2023-01-04";s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"3031176707";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9783031176708";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:213;s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:9:"Education";}s:11:"description";s:957:"This book is about the creation and production of textbooks for learning and teaching mathematics. It covers a period from Antiquity to Modern Times. The analysis begins by assessing principal cultures with a practice of mathematics. The tension between the role of the teacher and his oral mode, on the one hand, and the use of a written (printed) text, in their respective relation with the student, is one of the dimensions of the comparative analysis, conceived of as the ‘textbook triangle’. The changes in this tension with the introduction of the printing press are discussed. The book presents various national case studies (France, Germany, Italy) as well as analyses of the internationalisation of textbooks via transmission processes. As this topic has not been sufficiently explored in the literature, it will be very well received by scholars of mathematics education, mathematics teacher educators and anyone with an interest in the field.";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9783031176708-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=FM-lEAAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=FM-lEAAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:14:"epub_available";b:1;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";N;s:13:"ratings_count";N;s:9:"info_link";s:74:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=FM-lEAAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:59:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=FM-lEAAAQBAJ";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=FM-lEAAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:1;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:12;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"22CZEAAAQBAJ";s:5:"title";s:34:"Mathematics for Physical Chemistry";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:2:{i:0;s:18:"Robert G. Mortimer";i:1;s:12:"S.M. Blinder";}s:9:"publisher";s:8:"Elsevier";s:14:"published_date";s:10:"2023-02-20";s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"0443189463";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9780443189463";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:274;s:10:"categories";a:1:{i:0;s:7:"Science";}s:11:"description";s:1176:"Mathematics for Physical Chemistry, Fifth Edition includes exercises that enable readers to test their understanding and put theory into practice. Chapters are constructed around a sequence of mathematical topics, progressing gradually into more advanced material, before discussing key mathematical skills, including the analysis of experimental data and—new to this edition—complex variables. Includes additional new content on Mathematica and its advanced applications. Drawing on the experience of its expert authors, this book is the ideal supplementary text for practicing chemists and students wanting to sharpen their mathematics skills and understanding of key mathematical concepts for applications across physical chemistry. - Includes updated coverage of key topics, including a review of general algebra and an introduction to group theory - Features previews, objectives, and numerous examples and problems throughout the text to aid learning - Provides chemistry-specific instruction without the distraction of abstract concepts or theoretical issues in pure mathematics - Includes new chapters on complex variables and Mathematica for advanced applications";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9780443189463-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=22CZEAAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=22CZEAAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:14:"epub_available";b:1;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";N;s:13:"ratings_count";N;s:9:"info_link";s:74:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=22CZEAAAQBAJ&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:59:"https://play.google.com/store/books/details?id=22CZEAAAQBAJ";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=22CZEAAAQBAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:1;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:13;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"iAnMjwEACAAJ";s:5:"title";s:60:"Document concernant le film "Deux femmes sur les bras", 1927";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:0:{}s:9:"publisher";N;s:14:"published_date";N;s:7:"isbn_10";N;s:7:"isbn_13";N;s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:2;s:10:"categories";a:0:{}s:11:"description";N;s:9:"thumbnail";s:102:"https://books.google.com/books/content?id=iAnMjwEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=2&source=gbs_api";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=iAnMjwEACAAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=iAnMjwEACAAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:0;s:11:"viewability";s:8:"NO_PAGES";s:13:"pdf_available";b:0;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";N;s:13:"ratings_count";N;s:9:"info_link";s:100:"https://books.google.co.in/books?id=iAnMjwEACAAJ&dq=calculus+textbook&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:21:"canonical_volume_link";s:101:"https://books.google.com/books/about/Document_concernant_le_film_Deux_femmes.html?hl=&id=iAnMjwEACAAJ";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=iAnMjwEACAAJ&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:0;s:11:"viewability";s:8:"NO_PAGES";s:25:"text_to_speech_permission";s:7:"ALLOWED";s:13:"public_domain";b:0;s:13:"pdf_available";b:0;s:17:"pdf_download_link";N;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:18:"epub_download_link";N;}}i:14;a:21:{s:6:"source";s:12:"google_books";s:11:"external_id";s:12:"M73j2FlNKvAC";s:5:"title";s:17:"Integral Calculus";s:8:"subtitle";N;s:7:"authors";a:1:{i:0;s:11:"Hari Kishan";}s:9:"publisher";s:26:"Atlantic Publishers & Dist";s:14:"published_date";s:4:"2005";s:7:"isbn_10";s:10:"812690559X";s:7:"isbn_13";s:13:"9788126905591";s:8:"language";s:2:"en";s:10:"page_count";i:390;s:10:"categories";a:0:{}s:11:"description";s:1608:"The Present Book Integral Calculus Is A Unique Textbook On Integration, Aiming At Providing A Fairly Complete Account Of The Basic Concepts Required To Build A Strong Foundation For A Student Endeavouring To Study This Subject. The Analytical Approach To The Major Concepts Makes The Book Highly Self-Contained And Comprehensive Guide That Succeeds In Making The Concepts Easily Understandable. These Concepts Include Integration By Substitution Method, Parts, Trigonometrical Substitutions And Partial Functions; Integration Of Hyperbolic Functions, Rational Functions, Irrational Functions And Transcendental Functions; Definite Integrals; Reduction Formulae; Beta And Gamma Functions; Determination Of Areas, Lengths, Volumes And Surfaces Of Solids Of Revolution And Many More. All The Elementary Principles And Fundamental Concepts Have Been Explained Rigorously, Leaving No Scope For Illusion Or Confusion. The Focus Throughout The Text Has Been On Presenting The Subject Matter In A Well-Knit Manner And Lucid Style, So That Even A Student With Average Mathematical Skill Would Find It Accessible To Himself. In Addition, The Book Provides Numerous Well-Graded Solved Examples, Generally Set In Various University And Competitive Examinations, Which Will Facilitate Easy Understanding Besides Acquainting The Students With A Variety Of Questions.It Is Hoped That The Book Would Be Highly Useful For The Students And Teachers Of Mathematics. Students Aspiring To Successfully Accomplish Engineering And Also Those Preparing For Various Competitive Examinations Are Likely To Find This Book Of Much Help.";s:9:"thumbnail";s:71:"https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/isbn/9788126905591-M.jpg?default=false";s:12:"preview_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=M73j2FlNKvAC&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:11:"reader_link";s:83:"https://play.google.com/books/reader?id=M73j2FlNKvAC&hl=&as_pt=BOOKS&source=gbs_api";s:10:"embeddable";b:1;s:11:"viewability";s:7:"PARTIAL";s:13:"pdf_available";b:1;s:14:"epub_available";b:0;s:8:"metadata";a:13:{s:14:"average_rating";i:5;s:13:"ratings_count";i:1;s:9:"info_link";s:100:"https://books.google.co.in/books?id=M73j2FlNKvAC&dq